## WordPress Integration

### Overview

Tool pages are managed via WordPress REST API. Content templates in `content/tools/` are the source of truth. CLI tool handles push/pull operations.

### Commands

```bash
# List all WordPress pages
python scripts/wp_pages.py list

# Pull page to local markdown (overwrites local file)
python scripts/wp_pages.py pull --slug ai-pricing-calculator

# Push local content to WordPress
python scripts/wp_pages.py push --file content/tools/pricing-calculator.md

# Show diff between local and remote
python scripts/wp_pages.py diff --slug ai-pricing-calculator
```

### Content Template Structure

Every tool page has a markdown file in `content/tools/` with:

**Frontmatter (YAML):**

- `title` - Page title
- `slug` - URL slug (e.g., `ai-pricing-calculator`)
- `status` - `publish` or `draft`
- `seo_title` - AIOSEO title (under 60 chars)
- `seo_description` - Meta description (under 155 chars)
- `widget_endpoint` - API path for widget (e.g., `/pricing/widget`)

**Body sections:**

1. H1 title (same as frontmatter title)
2. Intro paragraph (2-3 sentences)
3. Widget marker comment
4. "How to Use" section (3 numbered steps)
5. "FAQ" section (4-5 Q&A pairs)
6. "Related Tools" section (links to other tools)

### Widget Embedding (Bricks)

In WordPress/Bricks, use a Code element with:

```html
<script src="https://ai-buzz-tools.onrender.com/embed.js" data-tool="error-decoder"></script>
```

Replace `error-decoder` with the tool name: `pricing`, `status`, or `error-decoder`.

The JS loader fetches widget HTML client-side, bypassing WordPress caching entirely. No more manual cache clearing needed.

### When Building a New Tool

After completing API and widget:

1. Create `content/tools/{tool-slug}.md` using `_template.md` as base
2. Write intro, FAQ, and SEO meta specific to the tool
3. Test locally, then push: `python scripts/wp_pages.py push --file content/tools/{tool-slug}.md`
4. In WordPress: Add script tag directly in page content (HTML block in Block Editor, or paste in Text mode in Classic Editor)
5. Verify page loads correctly at `ai-buzz.com/{slug}`

### When Cursor Should Help

- **Generate content:** When building a new tool, generate the content template
- **Optimize SEO:** Review/improve seo_title and seo_description on request
- **Add FAQ:** Add new FAQ entries based on common user questions
- **Push changes:** After editing content, remind to run push command
- **Pull updates:** If WordPress was edited directly, pull to sync local

### SEO Checklist

- [ ] seo_title under 60 characters, includes tool name
- [ ] seo_description under 155 characters, explains value
- [ ] Slug follows pattern: `ai-{tool-name}`
- [ ] FAQ includes "Is this tool free?" question
- [ ] Related tools links are accurate
